File: The Special Investigative Unit. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has instructed the Special Investigating Unit to look into allegations of corruption and maladministration in the Ekurhuleni Municipality and the Gauteng Agriculture Department. 
Ramaphosa also wants the unit to recover any financial losses suffered by government. READ: SIU investigators threatened The investigation will focus on a R27-million waste collection tender awarded to Enviro Mobi. The president wants to establish whether the procurement and payments made were done properly. Enviro Mobi reportedly has links to ANC spokesperson, Pule Mabe.